sieVvFwuObjectTable.description: Table of objects having updatable firmware.

sieVvFwuObject.description: Entry in Table of Firmware Update Objects

sieVvFwuObjectNo.name: sieVvFwuObjectNo
sieVvFwuObjectNo.description: Number of Table Entry: A unique value for each update object. Its value starts at 1. The value for each object may change during an update of the MIB data, i.e. at the date specified in sieVvLastDate.

sieVvFwuObjectName.name: sieVvFwuObjectName
sieVvFwuObjectName.description: Unique name to identify the updatable object within the server system: NT device name, with an extension in some cases such as a physical disk within a RAID array.

sieVvFwuObjectPath.name: sieVvFwuObjectPath
sieVvFwuObjectPath.description: Pathname to indicate more precisely the logical position of the object within the server system: e.g. bus path (including for example PCI bridge), SCSI target ID., etc.

sieVvFwuObjectParent.name: sieVvFwuObjectParent
sieVvFwuObjectParent.description: In some cases an object hierarchy has to be established for the purpose of updating firmware, e.g. a RAID controller which contains a physical disk, acting as a passthrough controller to that disk.

sieVvFwuObjectUpdateState.name: sieVvFwuObjectUpdateState
sieVvFwuObjectUpdateState.description: Specifies the state of this object with regard to update: 0 = normal, default state, 1 = cannot update now, e.g. a RAID rebuild is running, 2 = in the process of updating, 3 = error, update could not be completed successfully. 4 = update OK, but needs a reboot to become active, 5 = update OK, but needs a reset to become active.

sieVvFwuObjectComponentIndex.name: sieVvFwuObjectComponentIndex
sieVvFwuObjectComponentIndex.description: Value of sieVvInfoNo for the entry which describes the updatable object in the table of component information.
